AGI - The Israeli government confirmed the death of an Israeli held hostage in Gaza > by the Hamas attack on 7 October. Dror Or, 49 years old, was killed and his body was held in Gaza since October 7, > reported the kibbutz Be'eri where he lived, one of the most affected communities by the Hamas attack. His wife Yonat was killed in the assault, while two of their three sons, Noam and Alma, 17 and 13 years old, were kidnapped and then released in November > as part of a ceasefire agreement and exchange of hostages with prisoners between Israel and Hamas.
&nbsp;
"We have the heart broken in confirming the death of Dror Or, kidnapped by Hamas on October 7, murdered and whose body is still in Gaza," said the Israeli government on X, adding that "the two children and brother Yahli are now orphaned." The government did not explain how he learned about Or's death, announced while the Qatar, the United States and Egypt mediators expect Hamas' response to a new proposal to cease fire and release hostages.
&nbsp;
At the end of November, during a one-week ceasefire, 105 hostages were released, including 80 Israelis and people from other countries, in exchange for the release of 240 Palestinians held by Israel. The war began with Hamas' attack on Israel on October 7, which resulted in the death of 1,170 people, mostly civilians, according to an AFP count on Israeli official data. Israel estimates that there were 129 prisoners seized by militants in Gaza during the fierce attack. The army says 35 of them are dead, including Or. According to the Ministry of Health of the territory managed by Hamas, the Israeli retaliation offensive killed at least 34.596 people in Gaza, mostly women and children.&nbsp;

